<chapter xml:id="ch10-path-integral-formalism-dimension-1-alternative-" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Path Integral Formalism (Dimension 1 alternative)</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>This chapter explores a crucial dimension of the quantum framework. Develops Feynman's path integral approach as alternative to operator formalism, useful for fields and gauge theories.</p>
  </introduction>
  <section><title>Overview</title>
    <p>This chapter continues development of the 11-dimensional quantum framework. Key concepts and applications are developed systematically.</p>
  </section>
  <section><title>Core Content</title>
    <p>Detailed treatment of major topics and techniques for this domain of quantum mechanics.</p>
  </section>
  <section><title>Chapter Summary</title>
    <ul>
      <li>Key insight 1</li>
      <li>Key insight 2</li>
      <li>Key insight 3</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
